abstract: National Assn of Realtors releases report finding sales of existing homes in March reached highest level in 18 months, suggests economy is regaining momentum.
lead_paragraph: In a sign of a strengthening housing market, in March existing-home sales in the United States increased 6.1 percent to an annual rate of 5.19 million units.

headline.main: Home Sales Jump to Highest Level in 18 Months
headline.print_headline: Data From Realtors Points to Healthy Housing Market
